President Trump held a press conference in the Rose Garden to discuss the latest job numbers and the state of the economy. He touted the positive job numbers, stating that the economy is making a strong comeback after the COVID-19 pandemic. He mentioned progress being made on vaccines and therapeutics, and expressed optimism about the future. The President also emphasized the need to reopen the country and criticized governors who continue to have lockdown measures in place. He discussed the importance of equality and job opportunities for all Americans. The President signed legislation to make changes to the Paycheck Protection Program (PPP) to help businesses that have been impacted by the pandemic. Vice President Pence and other officials also spoke during the press conference.